@startuml
title Chatbot Flow Diagram

|Student|
start
:Open chat page;
if (Relevant session exists?) then (No)
  :Choose chat scope\n(All courses / Selected courses / Selected documents);
  :Create new chat session;
else (Yes)
  :Open existing chat session;
endif
:Enter and send question;

|Chatbot System|
:Send chat request with sessionId;

|System Handler|
:Authenticate user and verify session access;
:Check current plan quota\n(message count within 5-hour window);
if (Quota available?) then (Yes)
  :Persist user message into history;
  if (Is this the first message?) then (Yes)
    :Auto-generate session title;
  endif
  :Resolve document scope for the session;
  :Route intent\n(RAG QA or document metadata request);
  if (RAG retrieval required?) then (Yes)
    :Search document context within selected scope;
    :Generate answer and citations;
  else (No)
    :Generate metadata response\n(for example available documents);
  endif
  :Stream answer via SSE;
  :Persist assistant reply and increment quota counter;
  |Chatbot System|
  :Render streaming answer in real time;
  :Render citations and mark deleted sources when needed;
  |Student|
  :Read answer and citations;
else (No)
  :Build quota exceeded response;
  :Stream quota notification via SSE;
  |Chatbot System|
  :Show wait-for-reset or upgrade-plan notice;
  |Student|
  :Receive usage limit notification;
endif

stop
@enduml
